A popular Ghanaian pastor identified as Sylvester Ofori has been arrested after he reportedly murdered his wife in the United States.
 
The incident took place outside the 27-year-old woman’s workplace at the Navy Federal Credit Union, near the Mall at Millenia in Orlando, on Tuesday.  During a press conference, Chief Orlando Rolón said the shooting was captured on CCTV. “You can tell that she was surprised by what was happening,” he said.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .